<strong>ON LINE SIGN-UP INSTRUCTIONS          </strong></p>
<p>Please read all instructions carefully - THANKS!</p>
<p>Please rank the programs as the instructions describe: ranking only one program number 1, 2, 3, etc. for each child. Ranking more than one program #1, etc. for a child will be seen as a mistake and you will be contacted to revise your enrollment.</p>
<p>If your child does not get into all the programs that they initially enrolled in and you wish to enroll your child in additional programs at that point, you may contact the leader of those programs to ask them to enroll your child in those programs.</p>
<p>Please consider carefully the suitability of a program for your child before enrolling him or her in that program. Read the description carefully, especially the &#8220;Children Requirements&#8221;.<strong> If you have any questions about the suitability of a program contact the leader before enrolling.</strong></p>
<p>Please attempt to be realistic about the number of programs your family can comfortably attend. When the enrollment lists go out, leaders begin planning their class for the number of children that enroll. Although leaders are not all receiving a fee for their efforts, they are often putting a lot of preparation into their programs and deserve our consideration. When many families sign up for a program and decide not to attend without notification, it is very discouraging and inconvenient for the leader, and for the other families attending the program.</p>
<p>An increasing number of our programs utilize outside professionals and organizations, and we want to maintain a good reputation as an organization so that we can continue to utilize these resources and attract more outreach opportunities. This includes paying for programs on time, committing to attendance, and having students be a good match for the program.</p>
<p>We understand that familiesâ€™ schedules change and children&#8217;s interests change, and that some programs are not a good fit for certain families and children. Families will need to drop out of programs, and if you find you must do so, please contact the leader of the program as soon as you can. No explanation is necessary. It is important to notify the leader if your child decides not to attend a program at any point so that leaders can notify other children who may be on a waiting list for the program, and adjust their preparation for the program.</p>
<p>Thank you!</p>
