<p><strong>Childcare and Co-leaders   </strong><br />
Please take a minute to notice the support needs notes on each program   your children are signing up for.  If you see that your child has signed   up for a program that you can help with, please contact the leader to   let them know.</p>
<p><strong>FAQ:    </strong></p>
<p><em>1) How do adults sign up for programs?    </em></p>
<p>Sign up one of your children to hold your place in a   program for adults. Sorry there isn&#8217;t a more elegant   solution!</p>
<p><em>2) Are children &#8216;automatically&#8217; signed up for programs   that their parents are leading?    </em></p>
<p>No - if your child wants to attend a class that you   are leading, you should sign them up. Use zeros to enroll your child(ren) in your own programs.<br />
<em>3) Do I need to put a ranking number next to all the   classes we sign up for?    </em></p>
<p>No. You do not need to rank programs that have no size   limit. You can type a &#8216;0&#8242; (zero) next to any programs   that your kids are signing up for on the enrollment   form, where waitlisting is not a concern.</p>
<p><strong>Program Enrollment Process   </strong><br />
If a program receives more requests than the maximum   number of participants, children with the highest   interest ranking with get in first, and those with the   lowest interest will be waitlisted. Leader&#8217;s and   Parent Assistant&#8217;s children are always accepted   if they sign up for their parent&#8217;s class.</p>
<p><strong>Notification of Enrollment   </strong><br />
We plan to announce enrollment lists by March 31st-   this will tell you what classes your family got into   (and for leaders, who is enrolled in your program).</p>
<p><strong>Content of Programs   </strong><br />
Northern Light Learning Center is not responsible for   the content of classes or events. This responsibility   lies with the leader or co-leaders of a program. Talk   with the leader/instructor/ coordinator before you   enroll if you have any questions or concerns about a   given program.
